{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":944,"text":"Hi everyone."},{"time":3080,"text":"So, I'm going to take us back to 2007."},{"time":5920,"text":"I'd just spent about six months\nworking on album"},{"time":8200,"text":"that I'd poured my heart and my soul into,"},{"time":10280,"text":"and it was getting about three plays\nper day on Myspace at the time,"},{"time":13520,"text":"and I was getting more and more depressed\nwhen I started noticing these other people"},{"time":17560,"text":"who were playing guitar and singing"},{"time":19280,"text":"and putting videos\non this new site called YouTube,"},{"time":21720,"text":"and they were getting 300,000 views."},{"time":23480,"text":"So I decided I'm going to start\nmaking some Youtube videos."},{"time":26600,"text":"And one day they featured\na video of my band on the homepage,"},{"time":29840,"text":"which was amazing --\nwe got a bunch of new fans."},{"time":32119,"text":"We also got a bunch of people"},{"time":33560,"text":"who, I guess, just didn't really like\nthe music or something --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":36560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":37600,"text":"It's OK because people\nstarted coming to our shows,"},{"time":40040,"text":"and we started touring,"},{"time":41320,"text":"and we came out with a record."},{"time":42800,"text":"And when I checked\nour bank account balance"},{"time":44880,"text":"after our first monthly iTunes payout,"},{"time":46760,"text":"we had 22,000 bucks in it,"},{"time":48280,"text":"which was amazing because at the time\nI was living at my dad's house,"},{"time":51560,"text":"trying to make a living as a musician\nby uploading videos to the internet"},{"time":55040,"text":"which literally zero people\nrespected in 2009 --"},{"time":57880,"text":"even the people who were\nuploading videos to the internet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60640,"text":"And so for the next four years,"},{"time":62360,"text":"I uploaded more and more\nvideos to the Internet,"},{"time":65200,"text":"and they got better and better,"},{"time":67760,"text":"and we made enough money\nthrough brand deals"},{"time":70960,"text":"and commercials and iTunes sales"},{"time":73520,"text":"to buy a house."},{"time":75360,"text":"And we built a recording studio."},{"time":77680,"text":"But there was one big problem:"},{"time":79360,"text":"making money as a creative person\nin 2013 was super weird."},{"time":84480,"text":"First of all, the business models\nwere changing all the time."},{"time":87400,"text":"So our 58,000 dollars\nof annual iTunes download income"},{"time":91200,"text":"was about to be replaced by about\n6,000 dollars of streaming income."},{"time":94880,"text":"Steams paid less than downloads."},{"time":96800,"text":"And then as more and more creators\nstarted popping up online,"},{"time":99880,"text":"there was just more competition\nfor these five-figure brand deals"},{"time":103000,"text":"that had kept the band afloat for years."},{"time":105160,"text":"And to top it all off,\nour videos themselves --"},{"time":107400,"text":"the creative stuff that we made\nthat our fans loved and appreciated --"},{"time":111240,"text":"that were actually\ncontributing value to the world,"},{"time":113720,"text":"those videos were generating\nalmost zero dollars of income for us."},{"time":116880,"text":"This is an actual snapshot\nof my YouTube dashboard"},{"time":119280,"text":"from a 28-day period"},{"time":120560,"text":"that shows one million views"},{"time":122280,"text":"and 166 dollars of ad earnings\nfor those views."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126840,"text":"The whole machine in 2013"},{"time":129199,"text":"that took art online and outputted money"},{"time":132720,"text":"was totally nonfunctional."},{"time":135040,"text":"It doesn't matter if you're a newspaper,"},{"time":137600,"text":"or an institution,"},{"time":139240,"text":"or an independent creator."},{"time":140600,"text":"A monthly web comic\nwith 20,000 monthly readers --"},{"time":144920,"text":"20,000 monthly readers --"},{"time":146240,"text":"gets paid a couple hundred\nbucks in ad revenue."},{"time":148600,"text":"This is 20,000 people."},{"time":152080,"text":"Like, in what world is this not enough?"},{"time":155320,"text":"I don't understand."},{"time":157280,"text":"What systems have we built\nwhere this is insufficient"},{"time":160920,"text":"for a person to make a living?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":162960,"text":"So, I actually have a theory about this."},{"time":164920,"text":"I think it's been a weird 100 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":167920,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"About 100 years ago,"},{"time":171920,"text":"humans figured out how to record\nsound onto a wax cylinder."},{"time":175520,"text":"That was the beginning of the phonograph."},{"time":177520,"text":"Right around the same time,"},{"time":178880,"text":"we figured out how to record\nlight onto a piece of photographic paper,"},{"time":182200,"text":"celluloid -- the beginning\nof film and television."},{"time":184600,"text":"For the first time,\nyou could store art on a thing,"},{"time":187320,"text":"which was amazing."},{"time":188600,"text":"Art used to be completely ephemeral,"},{"time":190360,"text":"so if you missed the symphony,\nyou just didn't get to hear the orchestra."},{"time":193840,"text":"But now, for the first time,"},{"time":195280,"text":"you could store the orchestra's\nperformance on a physical object,"},{"time":199880,"text":"and like, listen to it later,"},{"time":201400,"text":"which was amazing."},{"time":203160,"text":"It was so amazing in fact,"},{"time":204440,"text":"that for the next 100 years,\nbetween 1900 and 2000,"},{"time":207760,"text":"humans built just billions and billions\nof dollars of infrastructure"},{"time":212280,"text":"to essentially help artists do two things."},{"time":214560,"text":"First, put their art on a thing,"},{"time":216640,"text":"and second, get that thing\naround the world"},{"time":218880,"text":"to the people who wanted the art."},{"time":220520,"text":"So, so much industry\nis devoted to these two problems."},{"time":223360,"text":"Oh my gosh, there are trucking companies,"},{"time":225337,"text":"and brick-and-mortar and marketing firms,\nand CD jewel case manufacturers,"},{"time":230040,"text":"all devoted to these two problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232840,"text":"And then we all know what happened."},{"time":235200,"text":"10 years ago, the internet matures"},{"time":236880,"text":"and we get Spotify\nand Facebook and YouTube"},{"time":238960,"text":"and iTunes and Google search,"},{"time":240800,"text":"and a hundred years of infrastructure"},{"time":243880,"text":"and supply chains and distribution systems"},{"time":246480,"text":"and monetization schemes"},{"time":248320,"text":"are completely bypassed --"},{"time":250240,"text":"in a decade."},{"time":252400,"text":"After 100 years of designing these things,"},{"time":255400,"text":"it's no wonder that it's just totally\nbroken for creative people right now."},{"time":259320,"text":"It's no wonder that the monetization\npart of the chain doesn't work"},{"time":262960,"text":"given this new context."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265520,"text":"But what gets me super excited\nto be a creator right now,"},{"time":270200,"text":"to be alive today and be\na creative person right now,"},{"time":273160,"text":"is realizing that we're only 10 years\ninto figuring out this new machine --"},{"time":279360,"text":"to figuring out the next 100 years\nof infrastructure for our creators."},{"time":283400,"text":"And you can tell we're only 10 years in."},{"time":285360,"text":"There's a lot of trial and error,\nsome really good ideas forming,"},{"time":288480,"text":"a lot of experimentation."},{"time":289760,"text":"We're figuring out\nwhat works and what doesn't."},{"time":292000,"text":"Like Twitch streamers.\nWho's heard of Twitch?"},{"time":294160,"text":"Twitch streamers are making\nthree to five thousand bucks a month"},{"time":297600,"text":"streaming gaming content."},{"time":298880,"text":"The big ones are making\nover 100,000 dollars a year."},{"time":303280,"text":"There's a site called YouNow,"},{"time":305000,"text":"it's an app."},{"time":306240,"text":"It allows musicians and vloggers\nto get paid in digital goods from fans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311040,"text":"So, I'm also working on the problem."},{"time":312800,"text":"Four years ago I started\na company called Patreon"},{"time":315160,"text":"with a friend of mine."},{"time":316440,"text":"We're 80 people now\nworking on this problem."},{"time":319440,"text":"It's basically a membership platform"},{"time":321720,"text":"that makes it really easy\nfor creators to get paid --"},{"time":324960,"text":"every month from their fans\nto earn a living."},{"time":327200,"text":"For a creator, it's like having a salary\nfor being a creative person."},{"time":331480,"text":"And this is one of our creators."},{"time":333080,"text":"They're called \"Kinda Funny.\""},{"time":334520,"text":"They have about 220,000\nsubscribers on YouTube."},{"time":337800,"text":"And when they upload a video,"},{"time":339240,"text":"it gets somewhere around\n15,000 views to 100,000 views."},{"time":342040,"text":"I want you to check yourselves right now."},{"time":344040,"text":"I think when we hear numbers like that,\nwhen we hear \"15,000 views,\""},{"time":347280,"text":"and we see content like this,"},{"time":348720,"text":"we just snap categorize it\nas being not as legitimate"},{"time":351920,"text":"as a morning show\nthat you'd hear on the radio"},{"time":354920,"text":"or a talk show that you'd\nsee on NBC or something"},{"time":357320,"text":"But when \"Kinda Funny\"\nlaunched on Patreon,"},{"time":359480,"text":"within a few weeks, they were\nmaking 31,000 dollars per month"},{"time":363760,"text":"for this show."},{"time":365280,"text":"It took off so fast that they decided\nto expand their programming"},{"time":368400,"text":"and add new shows,"},{"time":369680,"text":"and now they launched\na second Patreon page --"},{"time":372360,"text":"they're making an additional\n21,000 dollars per month."},{"time":376800,"text":"And they're scaling what's essentially\nbecoming a media company,"},{"time":381800,"text":"financing the whole thing\nthrough membership."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384400,"text":"OK, here's another example."},{"time":386160,"text":"This is Derek Bodner,"},{"time":387520,"text":"a sports journalist who used\nto write for Philadelphia Magazine"},{"time":390520,"text":"until a few months ago when\nthe magazine cut out all sports coverage."},{"time":393800,"text":"Now he writes articles\nand publishes them on his own website --"},{"time":396800,"text":"he's still covering sports,\nbut for himself."},{"time":398920,"text":"And he's making 4,800 bucks\na month from 1,700 patrons,"},{"time":401800,"text":"financing it through membership."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403800,"text":"This is Crash Course --"},{"time":405080,"text":"free educational content for the world."},{"time":407640,"text":"This show is actually\non the PBS digital network --"},{"time":410040,"text":"29,000 dollars per month."},{"time":411400,"text":"This is a duo sailing around the world,"},{"time":413640,"text":"getting paid every month\nfor documenting their travels"},{"time":416240,"text":"from 1,400 patrons."},{"time":417760,"text":"This is a podcast,\n\"Chapo Trap House\", making --"},{"time":420320,"text":"actually, since I screenshotted this,"},{"time":422200,"text":"they're making an additional\n2,000 dollars per month,"},{"time":424720,"text":"so they're now making 56,000 dollars\nper month for their podcast."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429200,"text":"And Patreon's not the only one\nworking on the problem."},{"time":431800,"text":"Even Google's starting to work on this."},{"time":433720,"text":"A couple years ago,\nthey launched Fan Funding;"},{"time":435920,"text":"more recently, they launched Super Chat"},{"time":437840,"text":"as a way for creators\nto monetize live streaming."},{"time":440240,"text":"Newspapers are starting\nto experiment with membership."},{"time":442840,"text":"New York Times has a membership program;"},{"time":444800,"text":"The Guardian has over 200,000\npaying subscribers"},{"time":447080,"text":"to its membership program."},{"time":448720,"text":"There's this bubbling soup\nof ideas and experiments"},{"time":453320,"text":"and progress right now,"},{"time":454840,"text":"and it's pointing in the direction\nof getting creators paid."},{"time":458320,"text":"And it's working."},{"time":459800,"text":"It's not, like, perfect yet,"},{"time":461400,"text":"but it's really working."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462880,"text":"So, Patreon has over 50,000 creators\non the platform making salaries --"},{"time":467760,"text":"getting paid every month\nfor putting art online,"},{"time":470840,"text":"for being a creative person."},{"time":473200,"text":"The next hundred years\nof infrastructure is on the way"},{"time":477680,"text":"and it's going to be different\nthis time because of this --"},{"time":480480,"text":"because of the direct connection\nbetween the person who makes the thing"},{"time":483880,"text":"and the person who likes the thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487320,"text":"About seven or eight years ago,"},{"time":489600,"text":"I went to a cocktail party."},{"time":492840,"text":"This is when the band\nhad hit our first machine,"},{"time":495120,"text":"so things were really cranking."},{"time":496640,"text":"We had just made\nabout 400,000 dollars in one year"},{"time":499040,"text":"through iTunes sales\nand brand deals and stuff like that."},{"time":501760,"text":"And this guy comes up to me and says,"},{"time":504560,"text":"\"Hey, Jack, what do you do?\""},{"time":505920,"text":"I said, \"I'm a musician.\""},{"time":508040,"text":"And he just sobered up immediately,"},{"time":511400,"text":"and he stuck out his hand,"},{"time":513440,"text":"put a hand on my shoulder,"},{"time":514720,"text":"and in a real earnest,\nvery nice voice he was like,"},{"time":518480,"text":"\"I hope you make it someday.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":519885,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":522880,"text":"And ..."},{"time":525240,"text":"I have so many moments like that\nlogged in my memory."},{"time":529320,"text":"I just cringe thinking of that."},{"time":532200,"text":"It's so embarrassing to just\nnot feel valued as a creative person."},{"time":539160,"text":"But as a species,"},{"time":540760,"text":"we are leaving that cocktail party behind."},{"time":543200,"text":"We're leaving that culture,"},{"time":545360,"text":"we're out of there."},{"time":547200,"text":"We're going to get so good\nat paying creators,"},{"time":549920,"text":"within 10 years,"},{"time":552200,"text":"kids graduating high school and college\nare going to think of being a creator"},{"time":556000,"text":"as just being an option --"},{"time":557280,"text":"I could be a doctor, I could be a lawyer,"},{"time":559257,"text":"I could be a podcaster,\nI could have a web comic."},{"time":561600,"text":"It's just going to be\nsomething you can do."},{"time":563680,"text":"We're figuring it out."},{"time":565440,"text":"It's going to be a viable and sustainable\nand respected profession."},{"time":569760,"text":"Creators are going to come out\nthe other end of this weird 100 years,"},{"time":573040,"text":"this century-long journey,"},{"time":575680,"text":"with an awesome new machine."},{"time":577840,"text":"And they're going to be paid,\nand they're going to be valued."},{"time":581760,"text":"Thanks, everybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":588360,"text":"I think it went pretty well."},{"time":591400,"text":"I want artists who saw that\nto not give up --"},{"time":595160,"text":"to know that we're getting there."},{"time":598720,"text":"It's not there yet,"},{"time":601360,"text":"but in a couple years,"},{"time":603280,"text":"there will be so many systems\nand tools for them"},{"time":605600,"text":"to just make a living online,"},{"time":607600,"text":"and if they've got a podcast\nthat's starting to take off,"},{"time":610920,"text":"but they're not able\nto make money on it yet,"},{"time":613080,"text":"that's happening"},{"time":614320,"text":"and they're going to be paid."},{"time":615760,"text":"It's happening."}]}]}